content:
OmniScripts Date Element

Enable users to select a date from a date picker by adding a Date element to your OmniScript. Set the minimum and maximum dates and the date format.

Drag a Date element from the Build panel onto the canvas.
In the Properties panel, give the element a name in the Name field.
In Field Label, enter a label visible to the user.
In Minimum Date, enter the earliest date the user can select from the date picker, such as 01-01-1950. 
You can pick a fixed date, or you can enter a relative date in the format TODAY +/- N day(s)/week(s)/month(s)/year(s).

The format entered must be the same as in the Date Format field.
In Maximum Date, enter the latest date the user can select from the date picker, such as 12-31-2019. 
You can pick a fixed date, or you can enter a relative date in the format TODAY +/- N day(s)/week(s)/month(s)/year(s).

The format entered must be the same as in the Date Format field.
In Date Format, enter the format to display the date.
(Optional) In the Advanced Options section, update values for Data Type and Model Date Format.
(Optional) Enter a Default Value. 
NOTE

The format entered must be the same as in the Date Format field.

You can pick a fixed date, or you can enter a relative date in the format TODAY +/- N day(s)/week(s)/month(s)/year(s). 

For example, to set the minimum date to January 1, 1950, if the Date Format is MM-DD-YYYY, you must enter 01-01-1950.
title: OmniScript Date Element Configuration
